name: ops::range::OneSidedRangeBound
doc_adt:
An internal helper for `split_off` functions indicating
 which end a `OneSidedRange` is bounded on.

VariantIdx(Some(0))-FieldIdx(None).name: StartInclusive
VariantIdx(Some(0))-FieldIdx(None).doc: The range is bounded inclusively from below and is unbounded above.

VariantIdx(Some(1))-FieldIdx(None).name: End
VariantIdx(Some(1))-FieldIdx(None).doc: The range is bounded exclusively from above and is unbounded below.

VariantIdx(Some(2))-FieldIdx(None).name: EndInclusive
VariantIdx(Some(2))-FieldIdx(None).doc: The range is bounded inclusively from above and is unbounded below.
